FBIS3-8339 "dreeu046_p_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-046 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Mar 1994 POLAND Echo TV in Wroclaw Asked To Stop Transmission LD0803193294 Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish 1600 GMT 8 Mar 94 LD0803193294 Warsaw TV Polonia Network Language: Polish Article Type:BFN [Text) The State Radio Communication Agency [PAR] has called Wroclaw Echo television to switch off the transmitter, which has been jamming Polsat programs on Channel 59 since 5 March. Echo has been a part of Polonia 1 network, and it said that it would not switch off. PAR threatens administrative measures because Echo has no franchise.
